quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  45,27,"God it is who has sovereignty over the heavens and the earth. On the day the Hour strikes, those who have denied His revelations will assuredly lose all"
  45,28,"You shall see each community on its knees. Each community shall be summoned to its Book: ‘You shall this day be requited for your deeds"
  45,29,This book of Ours speaks with Truth against you. We have recorded what you did.‘
  45,30,"As for those who believe and do good works, their Lord will usher them into His mercy. This shall be the veritable triumph"
  45,31,"As for the unbelievers: ‘Were My revelations not declared to you? Did you not scorn them and commit evil"
  45,32,"When you were told: \"God‘s promise is true: the Hour is sure to come,\" you said: \"We know nothing of the Hour. It is but a vain conjecture, nor are we convinced.\"‘"
  45,33,"The evil of their deeds will manifest itself to them, and the scourge at which they scoffed will encompass them"
  45,34,"They will be told: ‘We will this day forget you, as you yourselves forgot you would meet this day. The Fire shall be your shelter, and none will help you"
  45,35,That is because you scoffed at God‘s revelations and were seduced by your earthly life.‘ On that day there shall be no way out for them; nor shall they be asked to make amends
  45,36,"Praise, then, be to God, Lord of the heavens and Lord of the earth, Lord of the Universe"
  45,37,"Supremacy be His in the heavens and on earth. He it is who is the Mighty One, the Wise One"